Translumo-LLM Edition
=====================

Edition author : Chaobs (https://github.com/Chaobs)
Edition repo   : https://github.com/Chaobs/Translumo-LLM
License        : Apache License, Version 2.0 (same as upstream)


Summary of Changes (relative to upstream Translumo)
================================================

1. LLM AI translation backend (new feature)
   - Added a new translator type "LLM" (Translators.Llm) selectable in
     Languages -> Translator, alongside DeepL / Google / Yandex / Papago.
   - New namespace Translumo.Translation.Llm containing:
       * LlmProvider        : enum of supported providers
                              (DeepSeek, Qwen, Kimi, GLM, MiniMax, ChatGPT,
                               Claude, Gemini, Grok, Custom).
       * LlmApiStyle       : enum of API authentication styles
                              (OpenAi, Anthropic, Gemini).
       * LlmProviderPresets: default Endpoint / Model / ApiStyle per provider.
       * LlmConfiguration   : API Key, Endpoint, Model name, System prompt,
                              Temperature (default 0.3), MaxTokens (default 4096).
                              Persisted & AES-encrypted via ConfigurationStorage.
       * LlmContainer      : HTTP container reusing the existing HttpReader.
       * LlmTranslator     : translates text via chat-completions-style APIs,
                              with prompts tuned for video-game and film/TV
                              translation (terminology accuracy, context fit).
   - TranslatorFactory now constructs an LlmTranslator for Translators.Llm.
   - DI registration of LlmConfiguration in App.xaml.cs and
     ServiceCollectionExtensions.AddConfigurationStorage.

2. UI product name changed to "Translumo LLM"
   - ApplicationName resource set to "Translumo LLM".
   - Window titles: "Settings - Translumo LLM" / "Browser - Translumo LLM"
     (localized).
   - AssemblyInfo: AssemblyTitle / Company / Product = "Translumo LLM",
     version raised to 1.1.0, copyright updated to
     "Copyright (c) Chaobs (LLM Edition). Based on Translumo by
      Aleksei Vekhov & Danil Iushkov."

3. Project links updated
   - The bottom-left link on the settings window now points to the two
     GitHub repositories: this project (https://github.com/Chaobs/Translumo-LLM)
     and the original (https://github.com/ramjke/Translumo).

4. Localization extended
   - Added full Simplified Chinese (zh-CN), Traditional Chinese (zh-TW) and
     Japanese (ja-JP) translations covering all UI strings, the floating
     translation-window hints, the About dialog and the new LLM settings.
   - Languages can be switched in the settings window; the switcher lists
     languages by their native names (English / Русский / 中文 / 繁體中文 /
     日本語).
   - LocalizationManager.AvailableLocalizations now includes en-US, ru-RU,
     zh-CN, zh-TW, ja-JP.

5. About dialog updated
   - Shows "Translumo-LLM Edition" + version.
   - Credits the LLM Edition author (Chaobs) while preserving the original
     maintainer (Aleksei Vekhov) and original author (Danil Iushkov).
   - "Project page" and "Report an issue" point to this project's repository;
     the original project's links are preserved below.

6. Documentation
   - README.md updated for the LLM Edition and fork attribution.
   - This NOTICE file added to satisfy Apache License 2.0 attribution
     requirements for derivative works.


